header.gameNote: ATLANTIC SUN MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINALS AT MACON GA

article.headline: ETSU 72, Campbell 64
article.story: MACON, Ga. -- Micah Williams scored 32 points and sparked a second-half run to lead East Tennessee State to a 72-64 win over Campbell on Thursday in the first round of the Atlantic Sun Conference tournament. ETSU (18-14) advances to play in Friday's semifinals against Kennesaw State, who upset top-seeded Lipscomb 72-69 on Wednesday. Jacksonville will play the winner of Thursday's Belmont-Mercer game. Tommy Hubbard finished with 18 points for fifth-seeded ETSU, which was led by Williams' 10 points during a 12-2 run in the second half to help the Buccaneers claim a 58-47 lead with 5:01 left. Jonathan Rodriguez, one of 101 Division I players to ever score 2,000 points and grab 1,000 rebounds, ended his college career with 20 points for Campbell (19-11). Fourth-seeded Campbell led early through the first 26 minutes, but Williams' 3-pointer put the Buccaneers ahead for good.
